formula: Expansion of 6 + (eta(q) / eta(q^5))^6 in powers of q. - _Michael Somos_, Apr 30 2004
a(n) = A229793(n) - A078905(n) for n > 0. - _Seiichi Manyama_, Jan 01 2017
mathematica: a[ n_] := SeriesCoefficient[ 6 + 1/q (QPochhammer[ q] / QPochhammer[ q^5])^6, {q, 0, n}]; (* _Michael Somos_, May 22 2013 *)
program: (PARI) {a(n) = my(A); if( n<-1, 0, n++; A = x * O(x^n); polcoeff( 6*x + (eta(x + A) / eta(x^5 + A))^6, n))}; /* _Michael Somos_, Apr 30 2004 */
